File: Motjeka Madisha of Mamelodi Sundowns during the Absa Premiership 2019/20 game. JOHANNESBURG - The family of Motjeka Madisha has confirmed, that the Mamelodi Sundowns defender did die in a December accident.
This comes seven weeks after a fiery car crash in Kempton Park claimed the lives of two people. One of those was widely believed to be Madisha. At the time, his family had requested DNA tests to verify the identity of one of the bodies found at the scene. READ: Details of Madisha's fatal car crash emerge This was despite numerous people and organisations, including the South African Football Association, sending their condolences. Madisha will be laid to rest in Zebediela, Limpopo next Saturday. The 25-year-old was a regular in the Sundowns backline.